p:
Verticillium wilt is one of the major limiting factors of olive oil production and other than effects on crop yield, little is known about the effect of the disease on VOO quality and commercial value. In the context of the relationship between volatile and phenolic compounds and sensory characteristics in VOO (
 Angerosa et al., 2000; 
 Morales et al., 2013), we aim to study the effects of Verticillium wilt infection on these compounds as indicators of commercially important VOO quality.
